sidering using withFlags with a simple class. My plan is to utilize ClassFile.of().build(RESOLVED_CLASS, classBuilder -> classBuilder.withSuperclass(SUPER_CLASS)). It seems to default to object if no superclass is provided, which is good! I also need to think about a custom loader and ensure that I'm only testing the active class. It’s all pretty straightforward, but there’s a lot to keep track of!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Resolving class hierarchy issues**\\n\\nI'm working with ClassHierarchyResolver.ofResourceParsing(loader) and it returns an anonymous active class. I need to call getClassInfo and ensure that loader.resourceRequests equals 1, with the requested path being exact. I might determine the exact path from classDesc.descriptorString without importing any internal utilities. A helper function could assist in using a descriptor substring, but that feels like mimicking. If I call ClassDesc.of(\\\"example\\\", \\\"GeneratedChild\\\"), the resource would be \\\"example/GeneratedChild.class\\\", which is nice! I also need a custom classloader to serve this path.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Testing unknown classes**\\n\\nI need to test an unknown class, so calling resolver.getClassInfo(RESOLVED_CLASS) triggers the first test. I’m wondering if asserting null for an unknown class could trigger a second resource call, but the active call is already covered. More behavioral coverage might be beneficial! I need to rename ClassHierarchyResolver$2 to ClassHierarchyResolverAnonymous2Test and file this under src/test/java/io_smallrye_classfile/jdk_classfile_backport. I’ll make sure all top-level public classes are included, and private inner classes are fine. Don’t forget the copyright header—let's get writing!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_2xEZTDlaFAso5UjA1HRHHPyY|fc_00740f9c0fc860c10169f4090a46c881a2a6e3a6a888984ef5", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.smallrye.classfile/jdk-classfile-backport/26/src/test/java/io_smallrye_classfile/jdk_classfile_backport/ClassHierarchyResolverAnonymous2Test.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage io_smallrye_classfile.jdk_classfile_backport;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.lang.constant.ClassDesc;\n\nimport io.smallrye.classfile.ClassFile;\nimport io.smallrye.classfile.ClassHierarchyResolver;\nimport io.smallrye.classfile.ClassHierarchyResolver.ClassHierarchyInfo;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class ClassHierarchyResolverAnonymous2Test {\n    private static final ClassDesc GENERATED_CLASS = ClassDesc.of(\"example\", \"GeneratedChild\");\n    private static final ClassDesc SUPER_CLASS = ClassDesc.of(\"example\", \"GeneratedParent\");\n    private static final String GENERATED_CLASS_RESOURCE = \"example/GeneratedChild.class\";\n\n    @Test\n    void parsesHierarchyInformationFromClassLoaderResource() {\n        byte[] classBytes = ClassFile.of().build(\n                GENERATED_CLASS,\n                classBuilder -> classBuilder.withSuperclass(SUPER_CLASS));\n        InMemoryClassResourceLoader loader = new InMemoryClassResourceLoader(GENERATED_CLASS_RESOURCE, classBytes);\n        ClassHierarchyResolver resolver = ClassHierarchyResolver.ofResourceParsing(loader);\n\n        ClassHierarchyInfo classInfo = resolver.getClassInfo(GENERATED_CLASS);\n\n        assertThat(classInfo).isEqualTo(ClassHierarchyInfo.ofClass(SUPER_CLASS));\n        assertThat(loader.resourceRequests).isEqualTo(1);\n        assertThat(loader.lastRequestedResource).isEqualTo(GENERATED_CLASS_RESOURCE);\n    }\n\n    private static final class InMemoryClassResourceLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private final String resourceName;\n        private final byte[] classBytes;\n        private int resourceRequests;\n        private String lastRequestedResource;\n\n        private InMemoryClassResourceLoader(String resourceName, byte[] classBytes) {\n            super(ClassHierarchyResolverAnonymous2Test.class.getClassLoader());\n            this.resourceName = resourceName;\n            this.classBytes = classBytes.clone();\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public InputStream getResourceAsStream(String name) {\n            resourceRequests++;\n            lastRequestedResource = name;\n            if (resourceName.equals(name)) {\n                return new ByteArrayInputStream(classBytes);\n            }\n            return super.getResourceAsStream(name);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 904, "output": 1086, "cacheRead": 24064, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26054, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777600764614, "responseId": "resp_00740f9c0fc860c10169f408fd132881a2a55d525fedf1336e"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_2xEZTDlaFAso5UjA1HRHHPyY|fc_00740f9c0fc860c10169f4090a46c881a2a6e3a6a888984ef5", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 2574 bytes to tests/src/io.smallrye.classfile/jdk-classfile-backport/26/src/test/java/io_smallrye_classfile/jdk_classfile_backport/ClassHierarchyResolverAnonymous2Test.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777600780490}]}
